title: Fix multiple Swing rendering problems.  Closes #452.
message:
Fix multiple Swing rendering problems.  Closes #452.

Only call redraw() from the Swing event loop when it is not going to be
called from the game loop, because we are paused.

Refuse to actually do the re-drawing if another thread is already doing
it.

Launch a new thread when we do choose to redraw from within the Swing
event loop.

Do call this code when the window is activated as well as when it is
resized, to prevent not re-drawing when the window has been invisible.

This prevents lots of flickering when you resize on Swing, but makes the
paused game update itself, without ending up with a huge queue of
componentResized() events all waiting to do the re-drawing, as we saw in

title: Characters for water on ramps should follow the standard rules.
message:
Characters for water on ramps should follow the standard rules.

Previously we were trying to be clever and using N to mean the region was
full of water, taking into account the capacity. Now that we've implemented
the ability to specify standing water in a rel file, this is confusing, and
it's much simpler for N to always mean 1024 units, and n to always mean 512
units (unless specified otherwise by water description lines).

part of a solution command, but can't be run "at" a time step - instead

actions like PlaceTokenAction can be part of a solution command, and be
an action to be taken at a time step.
